Thousands of WhatsApp users reported major issues as the popular messaging app went down tonight. A total of 41,095 outages had been recorded by website monitoring service Downdetector as of 10pm on Thursday. The site showed issues with the app began at around 9, with most of the problems reported in London, Manchester and Birmingham. However, outages may be worldwide as the service tweeted from California to address the problem. The tweet said: ‘You may be experiencing some issues using WhatsApp at the moment. We’re aware and working to get things running smoothly again. We’ll keep you updated and in the meantime, thanks for your patience.’ WhatsAap was trending on Twitter as people took to the social media platform to air their annoyance. One wrote: “Me realizing WhatsApp is down after restarting my WiFi 50 times and uninstalling the app 6 times !!’ Another said: ‘Probably explains why my video calls were cutting off so often.’ Within an hour and a half of the problem being reported, the number of users experiencing a technical fault fell to 2,707. By 10.45pm, WhatsApp confirmed the issue had been resolved, tweeting: ‘And we’re back. Happy chatting.’ Facebook also seemed to be suffering smaller problems, with more than 200 users reporting an issue with the social network around the same time. Both are owned by Mark Zuckerberg’s Meta Platform. Got a story? Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. Or you can submit your videos and pictures here. For more stories like this, check our news page. Follow Metro.co.uk on Twitter and Facebook for the latest news updates. You can now also get Metro.co.uk articles sent straight to your device. Sign up for our daily push alerts here.